OPERATOR CONTROLS (real clickable software, not a movie)
- START/PAUSE cycle-hold button, first control in the HUD. Pause freezes
  dispatch, motion, and the VLM loop — but the shift clock, heartbeat, and
  ORDER DEADLINES keep burning. Pausing has an honest cost, like on a real
  line. Disabled during FAULT_ESTOP (that path has its own operator reset).
- Drag-to-re-plan: while paused, placed cartons glow blue and become
  draggable in the 3D scene. Drops settle via the same settleZ support math
  the optimizer uses; positions clamp to the pallet; the plan is the single
  source of truth so the arm's remaining picks re-target automatically on
  resume. Report card counts 'Cartons re-planned by hand'. Moves are blocked
  while running — verified.

REALISTIC CONVEYOR
- The belt now carries the REAL next cartons from the plan — correct
  dimensions and layer colors — not generic cubes. Belt slats visibly
  translate toward the pick point while the cell is MOVING and stop on
  pause/hold.

ADAPTIVE GRIPPER
- Vacuum plate and pad spread scale to each carton's actual footprint
  (clamped 0.7-1.6x) — the arm visibly adjusts its grip per box.
- Arm holds pose during pause, exception, and fault alike.

Verified: next build clean; node test — pause freezes placements while clock/
heartbeat/deadlines burn, moveBox applies only while paused with settleZ
heights, blocked while running, full shift to grade A report
